The lengths of these bases are $2 - \left( -\frac{7}{5} \right) = \frac{19}{5}$, $4 - 2 = 2$, and $4 - \left( -\frac{7}{5} \right) = \frac{27}{5}$, respectively.  The heights of the three triangles are $1 - 3 = -2$, $1 - 1 = 0$, and $1 - 6 = -5$, respectively.  Therefore, the area of the entire triangle is \[\frac{1}{2} \cdot \left( \frac{19}{5} \cdot 2 + 2 \cdot 0 + \frac{27}{5} \cdot 5 \right) = \boxed{9.80}.\]

