The intersection of $y = \frac{1}{2} x + 3$ and $y = -2x + 6$ is $(\frac{12}{5},\frac{21}{5}).$  Therefore, the area of the triangle is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot \left( \frac{12}{5} - 0 \right) \cdot \left( \frac{21}{5} - 1 \right) = \frac{102}{25}.\]To two decimal places, this is $\boxed{4.08}.$
